review_text:
Wow. I was really impressed. The man in front of me told me how it worked. I registered in minutes with a friendly staff member. Then a gracious volunteer told me to go to table 2 and within minutes I got really good food. I appreciate the food, the staff and all who volunteer there. God bless them.

It is now three years later. Didn't go very often until about a year ago. Didn't feel worthy. Mistaken ego. They have revamped it to make it even faster and better. Wonderful people, staff, volunteers, guards...all. God bless them.

review_text: SOVA Food Pantry has got to be one of the best in helping the homeless community and others who are going thru hardships due to the pandemic. folks can you be open for longer hours? Many of us recently lost our pandemic unemployement benefits and live on the street. In the heat walking sometimes it is hard to make it there by your place on foot.

some of us are really at times are starving..
I personally dont mind doing volanteer work for food. There are so many hungry people. But I have no car BMW repoed my vehicle when I lost my job last year and I got thrown out on the street..

So if possible please adjust the hours so we all can make it. Some of us dont have cars..and backpack is filled with clothing and we cant intake much food. So it would be nice if we can eat there at those tables..

name: Sova West Food Pantry
review_text: Not to make any excuses or beat it   like a dead horse. But I am having trouble understanding why they could not help me out. I understand they have rules to go by and they had to do what they had to do but they could have helped me out a little rather than hand me a list and basically tell me to kick rocks. I am a student, veteran, and a person who was having a little difficulty  this month. I do not go to food banks very often but I needed to go and I happened to pick their food bank but I had a zip code which was outside their area of service and I needed to go to another one of their phicalites to get food. Well list and out the door. I can understand in some respects becuase I do not have short hair and I am not clean shaven but to just basically be almost push out the door and made to feel unwanted I just want to thank them one more time. I am not mad but I am disappointed. But it is all good they do help other people I was just put in a category and pushed to the side and that is okay don't you think? Well I hope all of you have a good day. Marck Mueller

review_text: Staff and volunteers work tirelessly in highly coordinated chaotic environment with the patience and compassion of Angels to tailor make bags of groceries for low-income individuals and families and provide items that do not require facilities to cook for those that are homeless (homeless persons can visit the food bank twice per month!). On Thanksgiving, Hanukah and Passover the food bank gives out special bags of groceries to clients on a first come first serve basis. There are Social Workers available most days to provide assistance with a variety of benefits and sometimes a representative from PATH for those needing housing assistance.

name: Sova West Food Pantry
review_text:
The people who run this organization  are great.  They always try their best to reach out to the economically challenged of our society.  It is very commendable how they strive to make sure everyone is taken care of in getting food and things to help them along.  It is hard to complete this task daily especially when dealing with many different types of people and personalities.  It would help everyone involved if the people going to Sova to get help would just follow the instructions and get their numbers and remain seated until their number is called.  When they get their food they could take it with them outside and not create a back up chaotic situation for the next person in line.
Too many people are walking around and not sitting down or going outside to wait for their number to be called.   The security guard could step up and put the people who will not stay seated outside to wait in order to lessen the chaos for all involved.
Many times though, items asked for were not received and it was disappointing.  I think the chaotic situation causes the people filling the orders to become distracted which causes them to leave out things in orders or skim over some individuals orders leaving out key ingredients or items on orders.  This has happened many times.   Other than that the work of the people of Sova is commendable.

name: Sova West Food Pantry
review_text: I leave there with 4-5 bags of food and that includes bread, meat, chicken sometimes 2 bags of frozen fillet fish which I got last time. Also you can sign up to see a social worker to help and answer any questions you have. Plus there's one wall with different flyers pertaining to housing , emergency shelter , lawyer help, clothing , schooling , jobs Etc.... I can't say enough about this place , they are God's Angel's. 😇

name: Sova West Food Pantry
review_text: Very generous food bundles for needy families. Its a bit of a slow process to get registered and get your bundle. Best thing is that you can have choices so that you're not getting food that won't be eaten, you can select items, within reason. Most items are not canned foods, and meat and dairy items are included, along with some fruit & vegetables.
